FBIS4-51293 "drchi103_b_94012" FBIS-CHI-94-103 Daily Report 27 May 1994 United States & Canada President Clinton Names Aspin to Foreign Intelligence Board President Clinton Names Aspin to Foreign Intelligence Board OW2705053994 Beijing XINHUA in English 0501 GMT 27 May 94 OW2705053994 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Washington, May 26 (XINHUA) -- U.S. President Bill Clinton today named former Defense Secretary Les Aspin chairman of the Foreign Intelligence Advisory Board, which advises the President on top secret matters. Aspin, 56, succeeds Admiral William Crowe, who has become the U.S. Ambassador to Britain. Aspin became Clinton's defense secretary in December 1992 and retired earlier this year. He was succeeded by William Perry, the number two man at the Pentagon.
